sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant MC as MVNOClient
    participant CIF as CorrelationIdFilter
    participant SF as SecurityFilter
    participant TIF as TenantIsolationFilter
    participant DDC as DeviceDetailsController
    participant DDS as DeviceDetailsService
    participant VC as VendorClient
    participant VB as VendorBackend
    participant ALS as AuditLogService

    MC->>+CIF: GET /api/v1/devices?msisdn=+12125551234&mvno=MVNO-A<br/>X-API-Key: <key> (or Authorization: Bearer <jwt>)

    note over CIF: Read X-Correlation-Id header.<br/>Header absent → generate UUID v4.<br/>Set MDC[correlationId].<br/>Queue response header X-Correlation-Id.

    CIF->>+SF: forward request (correlationId in MDC)

    note over SF: Detect auth mechanism:<br/>X-API-Key header present → ApiKeyAuthFilter path<br/>Authorization: Bearer present → JWT path

    alt API Key authentication
        SF->>SF: Hash inbound key with BCrypt<br/>Lookup MvnoCredentialStore by hash<br/>Resolve MvnoCredential (mvnoId, credentialId)
        SF->>SF: Populate SecurityContext with<br/>Authentication(principal=MVNO-A, credentialId=...)
    else JWT Bearer authentication
        SF->>SF: Validate JWT signature against JWKS endpoint<br/>Extract mvno claim from token payload<br/>Populate SecurityContext with Authentication(principal=MVNO-A)
    end

    SF->>+TIF: forward request (SecurityContext populated)

    note over TIF: Extract authenticated MVNO from SecurityContext.<br/>Compare (case-insensitive) with mvno query param.

    TIF->>TIF: authenticated MVNO = "MVNO-A"<br/>requested mvno = "MVNO-A" → MATCH

    TIF->>+DDC: forward request (all checks passed)

    DDC->>DDC: Validate @RequestParam constraints<br/>msisdn matches E.164 pattern ✓<br/>mvno not blank ✓

    DDC->>+DDS: getDeviceDetails(msisdn="+12125551234", mvno="MVNO-A")

    note over DDS: Check cache (if enabled).<br/>Cache miss → proceed to vendor call.

    DDS->>+VC: fetchDeviceDetails(mvno="MVNO-A", msisdn="+12125551234")

    note over VC: Apply Resilience4j decorators:<br/>TimeLimiter(5s) + Retry(max=3) + CircuitBreaker<br/>Build WebClient request with vendor auth headers.

    VC->>+VB: GET /vendor/api/device?msisdn=+12125551234<br/>Authorization: Bearer <vendor-token><br/>X-Request-Id: <correlationId>

    VB-->>-VC: 200 OK<br/>{ subscriberId, msisdn, deviceName, manufacturer,<br/>  modelNumber, volteEnabled, imei, imsi, attributes }

    VC->>VC: Map HTTP 200 → VendorDeviceResponse<br/>Circuit breaker records success

    VC-->>-DDS: VendorDeviceResponse

    DDS->>DDS: ResponseMapper.map(vendorResponse, correlationId)<br/>→ DeviceDetailsResponse<br/>{ msisdn, mvno, deviceName, make, model,<br/>  hasVolte, imei, imsi, additionalAttributes, correlationId }

    note over DDS: If cache enabled → store DeviceDetailsResponse<br/>with key "MVNO-A:+12125551234", TTL=300s.

    DDS-->>-DDC: DeviceDetailsResponse

    DDC->>DDC: Set response header X-Correlation-Id from MDC<br/>Wrap in ResponseEntity<200>

    DDC-->>-TIF: ResponseEntity<DeviceDetailsResponse>(200)
    TIF-->>-SF: pass through
    SF-->>-CIF: pass through

    CIF->>CIF: Write X-Correlation-Id to response headers
    CIF-->>-MC: 200 OK<br/>X-Correlation-Id: <uuid><br/>Content-Type: application/json<br/>{ msisdn, mvno, deviceName, make, model,<br/>  hasVolte, imei, imsi, additionalAttributes, correlationId }

    note over ALS: AuditLogFilter captures: correlationId, timestamp,<br/>mvno, masked MSISDN, callerIp, credentialId,<br/>httpMethod, endpoint, responseStatus=200,<br/>durationMs, outcome=SUCCESS

    CIF-->>+ALS: AuditEntry(outcome=SUCCESS, responseStatus=200, durationMs=142)
    ALS->>ALS: Mask MSISDN: +12125551234 → +1212****1234<br/>Serialize AuditEntry to JSON<br/>Async write to audit log appender
    ALS-->>-CIF: (async, fire-and-forget)
